## Evolution: Applying the New Architecture Tasks

To adapt the base infrastructure to the updated project requirements, we execute a structural shift in how variables and locals are handled.

### 1. Declaring the Subnet Scaling Variable

Instead of locking the environment to a fixed count of 2, we introduce a dedicated input variable to drive the scaling engine. This can be configured in a `variables.tf` file:

```hcl
variable "subnet_count" {
  type        = number
  description = "The absolute number of subnets to spin up inside the VPC topology."
  default     = 2
}

```

### 2. Upgrading the Code to Match the New Task Specifications

To fulfill the requirement where the VPC and Subnets specifically pull fields from a distinct `local.project` variable and utilize our new input variable parameter, the code is refactored into this production-ready layout:

```hcl
locals {
  # New requirement fulfilled: Dedicated local project string
  project = "own_network"

  common_tags = {
    Project = local.project
    Name    = local.project
    Owner   = "own_terra_vpc"
  }
}

resource "aws_vpc" "own_vpc" {
  cidr_block = "10.0.0.0/16"
  tags       = local.common_tags
}

resource "aws_subnet" "dynamic_subnet" {
  # Replaced hardcoded 'count = 2' with the custom variable scaling parameter
  count      = var.subnet_count
  vpc_id     = aws_vpc.own_vpc.id
  cidr_block = "10.0.${count.index}.0/24"

  tags = merge(
    local.common_tags,
    {
      # Dynamically named tags via index tracks
      Name         = "${local.project}-subnet-${count.index}"
      ItemNumber   = tostring(count.index)
      FullDetails  = "${local.common_tags.Owner}-${count.index}"
    }
  )
}
